title: Generational shift as millennials make up half of new buy-to-let investors in England and Wales
summary: A surprising report from Hamptons reveals that individuals aged 18-34 account for 50% of all new shareholders in companies established this year. This trend indicates a significant shift in investment behaviors among younger demographics. The findings highlight the growing interest of younger generations in entrepreneurship and equity ownership.

title: Energy firms complete UK’s first ‘hydrogen blending’ trial to power grid
summary: A UK first has been achieved with a 2% blend of low-carbon gas injected into the gas grid to fuel the Brigg power station in North Lincolnshire. This initiative aims to reduce carbon emissions and promote sustainable energy sources. The project marks a significant step towards greener energy solutions in the UK.

title: Post-ministerial jobs watchdog closes as part of UK government ethics shake-up
summary: The Advisory Committee on Business Appointments (Acoba) will have its functions divided between two regulators following a recent decision. Additionally, a new Ethics and Integrity Commission will be established to oversee various other agencies. This restructuring aims to enhance oversight and accountability in public appointments.
